{# Recent-account-opening explanation panel — no source_ids to drill into.

  The detector fires when the statement period starts < 60 days before
  today. The card's description already explains the rule; this panel
  surfaces the concrete date and the operator playbook so a worker can
  decide in a glance whether the BUSINESS or just the bank account is
  new.

  Inputs:
    - card: PatternCard
    - analysis: AnalysisRow (optional; statement_period_start used in copy)
#}
<div class="evidence evidence-explanation">
  {% if analysis is defined and analysis and analysis.statement_period_start %}
    <p>
      Statement period starts <strong>{{ analysis.statement_period_start.strftime('%b %d, %Y') }}</strong> — under 60 days old, fails our 6-month intake baseline on its face.
    </p>
  {% else %}
    <p>
      Sub-60-day bank account — fails our 6-month intake baseline on its face.
    </p>
  {% endif %}
  <p>
    Today's review:
    <strong>(a)</strong> if the BUSINESS itself is also under 6 months → <em>decline</em>;
    <strong>(b)</strong> if the business is established (≥ 6 months) and merely switched banks → <em>request the prior bank's 3–4 statements</em> before declining.
  </p>
</div>
